#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""hapax-quota-telemetry-writer — live per-provider quota/resource telemetry.

Phase 0.4 (the designed R3 slice) of
REQ-20260609-model-capability-cost-routing-operationalization: the dispatcher's
quota state must come from live telemetry written on a timer, not from the
checked-in ``config/quota-spend-ledger-fixtures.json`` snapshot.

Each tick does two writes:

1. Refresh the per-provider platform capability receipts (quota / resource /
   capability surfaces) via
   ``scripts/hapax-platform-capability-receipts --all --codex-exec-auth-probe``.
   The registry freshness check reads these; the quota surface carries
   ``stale_after=15m``, so the paired systemd timer fires inside that window to
   keep subscription routes from HOLDing on ``quota_telemetry_stale_or_unknown``.

2. Rebuild the live quota/spend ledger at
   ``~/.cache/hapax/orchestration/quota-spend-ledger-live.json`` (or
   ``$HAPAX_QUOTA_SPEND_LEDGER_LIVE``). Governance records (transition budgets,
   dependencies, provenance, renewals) are carried over from the checked-in
   base unchanged. Spend receipts are carried over from the base plus validated
   GLMCP PAYG spend receipts reserved by ``scripts/hapax-glmcp-reviewer`` before
   a paid fallback call; telemetry never grants spend authority. The
   telemetry fields are re-derived live:

   - ``captured_at``: now.
   - subscription ``quota_snapshots``: per-platform state from the quota-wall
     relay receipts (``~/.cache/hapax/relay/receipts/<role>-quota-wall.yaml``,
     written by ``shared.quota_wall`` on observed 429/quota-exhaustion). An
     unexpired wall marks the platform ``exhausted`` on the subscription-wall
     path; Claude and GLMCP routes are ``unknown`` unless a fresh, short-lived
     route-specific admission receipt exists. Agy reviewer admission remains
     bounded to its sanctioned smoke receipt path. Other established subscription
     platforms remain wall-absence fresh until their route policy requires a
     receipt-bounded admission plane.
     Coding Plan quota walls block Coding Plan receipts, but a fresh
     endpoint-matched PAYG admission can supersede that subscription wall only
     when it is bound to the active Coding Plan quota-wall witness and a
     validated PAYG spend receipt reservation.
     Recheck admission evidence with
     ``find ~/.cache/hapax/relay/receipts -maxdepth 1 -name '*glmcp-quota-admission*.yaml' -print``
     and ``scripts/hapax-quota-telemetry-writer --json``.
     If a receipt exists but GLMCP remains ``unknown``, read this writer's
     stderr warnings; malformed, stale, mismatched, or unbounded receipts are
     ignored loudly.
     Recheck Claude and agy reviewer admission evidence with
     ``find ~/.cache/hapax/relay/receipts -maxdepth 1 -name '*claude-subscription-quota-admission*.yaml' -print``
     and
     ``find ~/.cache/hapax/relay/receipts -maxdepth 1 -name '*agy-quota-admission*.yaml' -print``
     and create fresh short-lived Claude admission receipts only after a genuine
     account-live subscription observation, or agy admission receipts only after
     a sanctioned ``scripts/hapax-agy-reviewer`` smoke succeeds.
     Admission receipts with ``stale_after_seconds`` above 3600 seconds are
     intentionally ignored; write a fresh short-lived witness instead.
     The emergency false-negative recovery path is to create a fresh
     short-lived admission receipt. Claude receipts must include schema, status,
     provider, capacity_pool, route_id, auth_surface, observation, observed_at,
     stale_after_seconds, evidence_ref, secret_source, secret_value_persisted,
     prompt_or_output_persisted, billing_mode, account_live_quota_observed,
     lane_presence_used_as_quota_evidence, and positive_admission. GLMCP/agy
     receipts additionally bind the reviewer tool/model/endpoint or smoke
     witness fields required by their scanners. Then rerun this writer so the
     live ledger is refreshed.
     That receipt-plane refresh is the canonical emergency procedure for a
     false negative.
     There is intentionally no environment-variable bypass for stale/unknown
     subscription quota. ``evidence_ref`` values are limited to 3-240 safe
     witness-reference characters.
   - ``spend_receipts``: base governance receipts plus GLMCP PAYG estimated
     spend receipts from ``*glmcp-payg-spend*.yaml``. These receipts are
     validated through the inert ``SpendReceipt`` model before they can reduce
     remaining paid-spend caps.
   - ``local_resource_state`` + local-compute snapshot: nvidia-smi VRAM
     pressure and load average, fail-closed to ``unknown`` when unprobeable.

The output is validated through ``QuotaSpendLedger.model_validate`` before an
atomic replace, so a bad tick can never clobber a good live ledger with junk.
No secrets are persisted. Capability receipt refresh performs bounded live route
probes where the route requires them: GLMCP invokes ``hapax-glmcp-reviewer
--check`` and Codex invokes the published-token ``codex exec`` auth witness.
Both record redacted availability metadata only; local resource probes remain
local files and nvidia-smi.
"""

